# Supabase — required for auth, feedback, and preference sync
# Get these from: https://supabase.com → your project → Settings → API
#
# Only VITE_-prefixed vars are exposed to the client bundle. The anon key is
# safe to ship to the browser; the service-role key MUST NOT be.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SERVER-SIDE ONLY — used by the `delete-account` Supabase Edge Function.
# DO NOT prefix with VITE_ and DO NOT put in Vercel client env: the service-role
# key bypasses Row Level Security and must never reach the browser.
#
# These are configured as Supabase *function secrets*, not in this file:
#   SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY are auto-injected
#   into deployed Edge Functions by the Supabase platform. If you need to set
#   them explicitly for local `supabase functions serve`, use:
#     supabase secrets set SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key
# (Never commit the actual service-role key to git.)
